# Medical Assessment App

A modern healthcare and medical assessments platform built with Next.js, React, Redux Toolkit, and Material UI.

## Features

- Next.js 15 app directory structure
- Redux Toolkit for state management
- RTK Query for API calls
- Material UI theming ([src/theme/theme.ts](src/theme/theme.ts))
- Authentication flow with cookie-based token ([src/middleware.ts](src/middleware.ts))
- Responsive design with custom CSS ([src/app/globals.css](src/app/globals.css), [src/app/page.module.css](src/app/page.module.css))
- Commitlint, ESLint, Prettier, and Husky for code quality

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- npm

### Installation

```sh
npm install
```

### Development

```sh
npm run dev
```

### Build

```sh
npm run build
```

### Start Production Server

```sh
npm start
```

## Project Structure

- [`src/app`](src/app) - Next.js app directory (pages, layouts, styles)
- [`src/components`](src/components) - Shared React components
- [`src/store`](src/store) - Redux store and API slice ([src/store/store.ts](src/store/store.ts), [`src/store/apiSlice.ts`](src/store/apiSlice.ts))
- [`src/theme`](src/theme) - Material UI theme ([src/theme/theme.ts](src/theme/theme.ts))
- [`public`](public) - Static assets

## Code Quality

- Lint: `npm run lint`
- Pre-commit hooks: Husky + lint-staged
- Commit message linting: Commitlint

## Environment Variables

Set your API URL in `.env.local`:

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-api-url.com
```

## Authentication

- Token is stored in cookies (`token`)
- Middleware in [`src/middleware.ts`](src/middleware.ts) protects routes

